text.section:
Subject to the hearing provisions of § 21-419 of this subtitle, the Secretary shall suspend a permit issued under this subtitle if:
The holder of the permit has obtained the permit fraudulently or deceptively;
The holder of the permit has violated this subtitle or a rule or regulation adopted under this subtitle;
A violation of this subtitle or a rule or regulation adopted under this subtitle exists at the place for which the permit has been issued under this subtitle;
A health hazard exists at the place for which the permit has been issued or exists as to the individual who holds the permit; or
The holder of the permit has interfered with the Secretary in the performance of the Secretary's duties.
